reviewText: I really liked the first volume, but I love this one. It has some of my favorite bands, and I love Miku as the host. I was very pleased.

Being a big fan of An Cafe.  I really like how this DVD is hosted by the lead singer MIKU.  But if your a fan of Visual-Kei, you'll definitely like this DVD.  The interview with the bands are great, I especially like that part when the band SMILE was eating at the sushi shop, it was pretty entertaining.
This is a good product.  It was just a matter of not liking some of the bands as much as the first one.

This one was not as good as the first one.  In fact, I skipped through most of it.  It is still worth buying as an introduction to some current JRock/Visual bands, but there is nothing memorable about it.
